insights: To succeed, you must be willing to do whatever it takes and put in the effort to achieve your goals.
Your job and how you execute it will create the success habits you need to achieve long-term success.
How you do one thing is how you do everything, so focus on making the best of every situation.
Losers talk about wanting to win but don't take action, while winners take consistent action and make sacrifices to achieve their goals.
To be the best, you must be willing to put in the time and effort to outwork others and stay ahead of the competition.
The key to success is not just about being the best, but also about being dominant and taking pride in your work.
The difference between winners and losers is not talent or ability, but rather the willingness to work hard and make sacrifices to achieve success.
